  "findings": {
    "signal_quality": "STRONG for RentCafe-powered sites. The GA4 analytics data attributes (setGA4Cookie) embed structured floorplan data directly in HTML: name, beds, sqft_min, sqft_max, rent_min, rent_max. This is more reliable than free-text extraction — it's machine-readable data embedded for analytics tracking. An appraiser would immediately recognize this as usable comp data.",
    "coverage": "3 of 20 discovered properties (15%) yielded usable rent data. 75% of discovered properties have no website at all (typical for small Hawthorne apartment buildings). Of the 5 with websites: 2 high-confidence extractions, 1 unit-mix-only (fully occupied), 1 management company site (wrong URL), 1 blocked (403).",
    "platform_insight": "All 3 successful extractions were RentCafe (Yardi) sites. RentCafe is the dominant platform for institutional multifamily — this is a significant finding. A production harvester could specifically target the RentCafe /floorplans page structure and GA4 data attributes for highly reliable extraction without needing LLM parsing at all.",
    "failure_modes": [
      "75% of apartment communities have no website (small/independent operators)",
      "Laurel Pointe returned 403 — blocks automated requests",
      "Bay Pointe's Google Places 'website' pointed to management company, not property",
      "Lemoli had $0 rents — fully occupied, no current pricing",
      "Places API (New) not enabled — legacy API needed Text Search workaround",
      "Legacy Nearby Search 'type=apartment_complex' returned hotels/stores (useless)"
    ],
